            <title>[SOLR-16145] Overseer rejoinOverseerElection NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16145</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13410&quot; title=&quot;Designated overseer not able to become overseer quickly &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-13410&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-13410&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, an NPE can occur if &lt;tt&gt;overseerElector.getContext().leaderSeqPath&lt;/tt&gt; is null.  I observed this in a test.  The fix looks clear; the null check is inverted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
